I had undergone angiography and stent implantation during 2006. Procedure done by Dr. Shyam Sundar. Since then I have been visiting him twice annually for regular check up . I find him very friendly towards patients. A simple person with lot of care and love towards his patients. Slowly hears the patient's problems and comes out with good medications.

****** **** ****** *********** * ******** ******** *** **** The doctor could guide patient or its designate on how to take medicines like before food or after food and number of days the medicine needs to be taken. Ambience is not great. Lots of mosquitos.

Had appointments on 2 days in the week. On one of the days, doctor was on time and on the other day, doctor arrived more than 30 mins late. Doctor did a preliminary health check on BP, physical examination and then sent us for blood test, echo and TMT. Reports were quickly obtained and doctor gave his diagnosis quickly. His experience makes *** ********* ********, quick and to the point.

Waiting period for TMT or echo cardiogram ma be reduced.
While technicians at TMT or echo cardiogram are very friendly, process of seeking prior appointment at least one day in advance may be introduced,instead of taking appointment on the same day.
Very satisfying consultation.. recovered from critical emergency.. our family is blessed to have such a great doctor

** ***** ** *** ** *** **** ******* *** I have received excellent advises and recommendations from him.
